    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in nr_polar_rate_matching_int16 when i_bil=1\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_polar_rate_matching_int16` function in the polar coding procedures was experiencing undefined behavior and producing incorrect results when `i_bil=1` due to improper buffer handling in the rate matching deinterleaving operation.\n\nWhen processing polar coded data with bit interleaving enabled, the function would call `nr_polar_rm_deinterleaving_cb(input, input, E)` with the same buffer for both input and output parameters. However, the deinterleaving function modifies the data while reading from it, causing data corruption and unpredictable decoder behavior.\n\nThis issue manifests as incorrect polar decoding results, particularly affecting PBCH and DCI processing where i_bil=1 is used for rate matching. Users may observe:\n- UE failing to synchronize with gNB\n- Random access failures\n- DCI detection and decoding failures\n- Inconsistent CRC validation results\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrPolar_tools/nr_polar_procedures.c`: Modified `nr_polar_rate_matching_int16` to use a temporary buffer when `i_bil=1` to prevent self-modification during deinterleaving\n- Added bounds checking to prevent potential buffer overflows in rate matching pattern access\n- Improved error handling for memory allocation failures\n\n"
}